Here's a R code that shuffles the elements of a given vector:

```R
shuffle_vector <- function(vector) {
  if (length(vector) == 0) {
    return("The vector is empty. Please provide a non-empty vector.")
  }

  n <- length(vector)
  shuffled_vector <- vector

  for (i in 1:(n-1)) {
    j <- sample(i:n, 1)
    temp <- shuffled_vector[i]
    shuffled_vector[i] <- shuffled_vector[j]
    shuffled_vector[j] <- temp
  }

  return(shuffled_vector)
}

