The function uses a simple algorithm known as Fisher-Yates shuffle. It iterates over the vector from the first element to the second-to-last element. For each iteration, it generates a random index `j` between the current position `i` and the last position `n`. It then swaps the elements at positions `i` and `j`. This process is repeated until all elements have been shuffled.

Finally, the function returns the shuffled vector.

