Here is a C program that finds the longest word in a sentence without using any built-in string length functions or methods. It also handles cases where there are multiple words with the same length and ignores punctuation marks or special characters.

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int isPunctuation(char c) {
    return (c == '!' || c == '?' || c == '.' || c == ',' || c == ';' || c == ':');
}

void longestWord(char *sentence) {
    int maxLength = 0;
    int currentLength = 0;
    int longestWordIndex = -1;
    int error = 0;
    int i;

    for (i = 0; sentence[i] != '\0'; i++) {
        if (isPunctuation(sentence[i])) {
            // Ignore punctuation marks
            continue;
        }

        if (sentence[i] == ' ') {
            if (currentLength > maxLength) {
                maxLength = currentLength;
                longestWordIndex = i - currentLength;
                error = 0;
            } else if (currentLength == maxLength) {
                error = 1;
            }

            currentLength = 0;
        } else {
            currentLength++;
        }
    }

    // Check the last word in case it is the longest
    if (currentLength > maxLength) {
        maxLength = currentLength;
        longestWordIndex = i - currentLength;
        error = 0;
    } else if (currentLength == maxLength) {
        error = 1;
    }

    if (error) {
        printf("Error: Multiple words have the same length.\n");
    } else if (longestWordIndex >= 0) {
        printf("The longest word is: ");
        for (i = longestWordIndex; i < longestWordIndex + maxLength; i++) {
            printf("%c", sentence[i]);
        }
        printf("\n");
    } else {
        printf("No words found.\n");
    }
}

int main() {
    char sentence[100];

    printf("Enter a sentence: ");
    fgets(sentence, sizeof(sentence), stdin);

    longestWord(sentence);

    return 0;
}
```

In this program, the `isPunctuation` function checks if a given character is a punctuation mark. The `longestWord` function finds the longest word in the sentence by iterating through each character and updating the length of the current word. It also keeps track of the index of the longest word and sets an error flag if multiple words have the same length.

