The time complexity of the revised code is O(n log n) for adding tasks to the queue and O(n log n) for executing tasks, where n is the number of tasks. The space complexity is O(n) to store the tasks in the queue.

To further optimize the code, a data structure like a binary heap can be used instead of a priority queue to improve the efficiency of adding tasks. Additionally, if the task queue is frequently modified, a self-balancing binary search tree like AVL tree or Red-Black tree can be used for efficient task insertion and removal operations.

