The `findMaximumOddPrime` method takes the array `arr` and the start and end indices of the current subarray as parameters. It uses recursion to divide the subarray into smaller subarrays until there is only one element. Then, it checks if the element is both odd and prime. If it is, the index of the element is added to the `indices` list.

After finding the maximum odd prime elements in the left and right subarrays, the method compares the maximum values and selects the overall maximum odd prime value. Finally, it checks if the maximum odd prime element in the current subarray satisfies the criteria and adds its index to the `indices` list if it does.

The `isOdd` method checks if a number is odd by checking if the remainder of dividing it by 2 is not equal to 0. The `isPrime` method checks if a number is prime by iterating from 2 to the square root of the number and checking if any of the numbers divide the given number without a remainder.

